From: Borislav Petkov <bp@suse.de>
Date: Mon, 31 Oct 2016 16:10:15 +0100
Subject: x86/copy_user: Unify the code by removing the 64-bit asm
 _copy_*_user() variants
Git-commit: adb402cd1461eef6e1a21db4532a3b9e6a6be853
Patch-mainline: v4.10-rc1
References: bsc#1211738 CVE-2023-0459

We already have the same functionality in usercopy_32.c. Share it with
64-bit and get rid of some more asm glue which is not needed anymore.

